    "(2.27) and up to gradient order we have,P del ≈ W E (P len + P noise)(n -W ϕ (∇ φ + O(∇ φ) 2)) ≈ W E (P len + P noise)(n) -W E W ϕ ∇(P len + P noise)(n)∇(ϕ + ϕ noise) = W E P len -W E W ϕ ∇P len ∇ϕ + W E P noise -W E W ϕ ∇P noise (∇ϕ + ∇ϕ noise) + W E W ϕ ∇P len ∇ϕ noise, (4.8)Notice that we have neglected high-order terms since the second line, andW E = C EE ℓ /(C EE ℓ + N EE ℓ)in the first term of the third line is close to unity because the E-mode signal is much stronger than its noise.",
    "Therefore, up to the gradient order, these delensing noise bias of the two methods is nearly equal.",
    "However, as discussed in Section 2.3.3, it is the noise bias on small scales arising from the neglected high-order terms in Eq.",
